---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Services - SkanPay"
  description="Explore SkanPay services for in-store QR payments, payment gateway integration, merchant onboarding, and partner support."
  activePath="/services/"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Services</p>
    <h1>QR payment services for merchants and payment partners</h1>
    <p>SkanPay supports conversations around in-store QR payment acceptance, gateway workflows, merchant onboarding, and wallet or loyalty partnerships.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid two">
      <article class="card route-card">
        <span>Service</span>
        <h3>In-store QR payments</h3>
        <p>Define how a QR payment request appears at checkout and what staff should expect after scan.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card route-card">
        <span>Gateway</span>
        <h3>Payment gateway integration</h3>
        <p>Map transaction status, customer authorization, and merchant confirmation requirements.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card route-card">
        <span>Operations</span>
        <h3>Merchant onboarding</h3>
        <p>Plan store setup, staff guidance, checkout messaging, and support escalation steps.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card route-card">
        <span>Partner</span>
        <h3>Loyalty and wallet partnerships</h3>
        <p>Clarify where payment apps, wallets, and loyalty programs participate in the transaction.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Operational fit</p>
      <h2>Keep the checkout experience understandable</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">A QR payment service only works when the merchant, customer, and payment partner all know what is supposed to happen next.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="split-panel">
      <h3>Service conversations can include</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Store-level QR payment use cases and checkout constraints</li>
        <li>Customer scan, review, authorization, and cancellation states</li>
        <li>Merchant-facing confirmation, pending, and failure handling</li>
        <li>General reporting and settlement expectations, kept scope-accurate</li>
        <li>Partner or wallet integration boundaries</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
